e formal [[financial system]].<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://nation.com.pk/06-Feb-2020/sadapay-to-offer-online-payments-through-mastercard-network-and-hassle-free-international-deposits|title=SadaPay to offer online payments through MasterCard network, international deposits|date=2020-02-06|website=The Nation|language=en|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref> In partnership with [[Mastercard|MasterCard]], SadaPay is issuing physical debit cards tied to a free digital wallet that allows customers to shop in stores or online, anywhere in the world.<ref name=\":1\" /> Brandon is joined by senior-level Pakistani ex-bankers, and a foreign technology team. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://profit.pakistantoday.com.pk/2020/02/05/sadapay-another-mobile-wallet-aims-to-disrupt-local-banking/|title=SadaPay, another mobile wallet, aims to disrupt local banking|last=Hassan|first=Taimoor|date=2020-02-05|website=Profit by Pakistan Today|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\nInspired by [[Travis Kalanick]] of [[Uber|Uber]], Timinsky co-founded GasNinjas in 2015 with Barret Hammond.<ref name=\":0\" /> The business merged with Exajoule, an energy company.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Timinsky, Brandon}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Businesspeople from Miami]]\n[[Category:1991 births]]\n[[Category:University of Miami Business School alumni]]\n[[Category:Florida International University alumni]]\n", "name_user": "Llohcs", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brandon_Timinsky"}
